---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="1RM Formula Explanations" 
  description="Learn about the four proven formulas for calculating one-rep max: Epley, Brzycki, Lombardi, and O'Conner. Understand their accuracy, validity ranges, and when to use each method."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto p-6">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li><a href="/" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium transition-colors duration-200">1RM Calculator</a></li>
        <li class="before:content-['/'] before:mr-2">Formula Explanations</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-gray-50 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100 p-8 mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-4">1RM Formula Explanations</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Our calculator uses four proven scientific formulas to estimate your one-rep max. Each has different strengths and optimal rep ranges for maximum accuracy.
      </p>

      <!-- Formula Cards -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Epley Formula -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-8 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Epley Formula</h2>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6 border border-blue-100">
            <code class="text-xl font-mono text-blue-800 font-bold">1RM = Weight × (1 + Reps/30)</code>
          </div>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Best for:</h3>
              <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Moderate rep ranges (3-8 reps)</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>General strength training</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Most common and widely used</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Accuracy:</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Very reliable for 3-8 reps. Tends to slightly overestimate at very low reps (1-2) and underestimate at higher reps (9-12).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Brzycki Formula -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-8 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Brzycki Formula</h2>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6 border border-green-100">
            <code class="text-xl font-mono text-green-800 font-bold">1RM = Weight × 36 / (37 - Reps)</code>
          </div>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Best for:</h3>
              <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Lower rep ranges (1-6 reps)</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Powerlifting movements</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Maximum strength testing</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Accuracy:</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Most accurate for 1-6 reps. Becomes less reliable above 8 reps. Preferred by powerlifters for its accuracy at low rep ranges.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Lombardi Formula -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-8 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Lombardi Formula</h2>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-pink-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6 border border-purple-100">
            <code class="text-xl font-mono text-purple-800 font-bold">1RM = Weight × Reps^0.10</code>
          </div>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Best for:</h3>
              <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Single rep attempts</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Elite level athletes</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Validation of other formulas</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Accuracy:</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Most conservative estimate. Often underestimates true 1RM, especially for higher rep ranges. Good as a safety baseline.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- O'Conner Formula -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-8 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">O'Conner Formula</h2>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-50 to-red-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6 border border-orange-100">
            <code class="text-xl font-mono text-orange-800 font-bold">1RM = Weight × (1 + 0.025 × Reps)</code>
          </div>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Best for:</h3>
              <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Higher rep ranges (6-12 reps)</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Bodybuilding movements</li>
                <li class="flex items-center"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-500 rounded-full mr-3"></span>Endurance-strength training</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-lg">Accuracy:</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                More conservative than Epley. Works well for moderate to higher rep ranges. Often preferred for safety when working with novice lifters.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Table -->
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Comparison</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Formula</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Best Rep Range</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Tendency</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Use Case</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Epley</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">3-8 reps</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Moderate estimate</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">General training</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Brzycki</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">1-6 reps</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Higher estimate</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Powerlifting</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Lombardi</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">1-3 reps</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Conservative</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Safety baseline</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">O'Conner</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">6-12 reps</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Conservative</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600">Higher rep training</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Important Notes -->
      <div class="mt-8 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-3">Important Considerations</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-yellow-700">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 mr-2">•</span>
            <span><strong>Rep Range Matters:</strong> All formulas become less accurate beyond 12 reps. For best results, test between 1-10 reps.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 mr-2">•</span>
            <span><strong>Individual Variation:</strong> Your actual 1RM may differ based on training background, muscle fiber type, and lifting technique.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 mr-2">•</span>
            <span><strong>Exercise Specificity:</strong> Formulas work best for compound movements (squat, bench, deadlift) and may be less accurate for isolation exercises.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 mr-2">•</span>
            <span><strong>Safety First:</strong> These are estimates. Always warm up properly and consider having a spotter for maximum attempts.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Navigation -->
      <div class="mt-8 flex justify-between">
        <a href="/" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">← Back to Calculator</a>
        <a href="/faq/" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">FAQ →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>